1. change your data.sql file name to schema.sql (cuz u r creating table not populating data) and change value to val to avoid reserved keyword errors

```
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `Tags` (
    id			INTEGER  PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
    `val`		    VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    background	VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL,
    font		VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL
);
```

2. add both those lines to your application properties

`spring.sql.init.mode=always` to tell springboot to use schema.sql file and also data.sql if exists.

`spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=none` to prevent hibernate from trying to create schema from Entities.
 
3. in Tag class use the @Table and @Column annotations to match schema.sql file
```
@Entity
@Table(name = &quot;Tags&quot;)
public class Tag {
	@Column(name = &quot;val&quot;)
	private String value;
}
```

