You can also do it by just converting the String values to decimal imperatively using a loop. Here is how it works.  Consider `0x2AF` and starting with `2`.
```
v = 0   // initialize v
v = v * 16 + 2  (0*16) + 2 = 0 + 2
v = v * 16 + 10 (2* 16) + 10 =32 + 10 = 42
v = v * 16 + 15 (42*16) + 15 = 672 + 15 = 687
```
- first declare a string of hex digits
- the index of each is their decimal equivalent
- Converting to uppercase, repeat the previously demonstrated process.
```
String hexDigits = &quot;0123456789ABCDEF&quot;;
for (String hex : hexValues) {
     int value = 0;
     for (char c : hex.toUpperCase().toCharArray()) {
         int index = hexDigits.indexOf(c);
         if (index &gt;= 0) {
             value = value * 16 + index; 
         }
     }
     ints.add(value);
}

